			<div class="post-2107 post hentry category-uncategorized teaser" id="post-2107">
<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.cookthink.com/blog/2011/01/2107/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to Warm Potato Salad (update)">Warm Potato Salad (update)</a></h2>
<abbr class="teaser_date published" title="2011-01-09">January 9, 2011</abbr>

				<div class="format_teaser entry-content">
<p>I think I learned the general idea from Alice Waters: dress vegetables you want to treat as a salad (especially where vinegar is involved ) while hot. Here it was whole grain mustard, mayonnaise, buttermilk, white wine vinegar and red pepper flakes. About to add some chopped dill this to round it out.</p>
				</div>
<a class="teaser_link" href="http://www.cookthink.com/blog/2011/01/2107/" rel="nofollow">[Continue reading]</a>
			</div>

			<div class="post-2102 post hentry category-uncategorized teaser teaser_right" id="post-2102">
<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.cookthink.com/blog/2011/01/warm-potato-salad/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to Warm Potato Salad">Warm Potato Salad</a></h2>
<abbr class="teaser_date published" title="2011-01-09">January 9, 2011</abbr>

				<div class="format_teaser entry-content">
<p>About to roast these guys &#8211; fingerlings. Tossed them with salt, pepper, and a little anchovy oil. Got a buttermilk, mayo, lemon dressing waiting for them. Total spur-of-the-moment. Also got some baby-back ribs marinating in ginger and soy. Thinking about firing up the grill.</p>
				</div>
<a class="teaser_link" href="http://www.cookthink.com/blog/2011/01/warm-potato-salad/" rel="nofollow">[Continue reading]</a>
